{{Quote|It makes perfect sense that [[Kate Bishop|she]] would be hostile. She likely feels displaced by me, and she's testing our new dynamic. She both desires my approval, yet wants to set firm boundaries. She feels threatened by me, and you know what? I can understand why.|Jack Duquesne to [[Eleanor Bishop]]|Hide and Seek}}
'''Jacques "Jack" Duquesne''' is a wealthy socialite and talented swordsman who became engaged to [[Eleanor Bishop]]. In [[2024|December 2024]], Jack was suspected by Eleanor's daughter [[Kate Bishop]] when his uncle [[Armand Duquesne III]] was [[Assassination of Armand Duquesne III|murdered]]. However, Eleanor did it and framed Jack for his death, and also pinned his name to a [[Sloan Limited|shell corporation]] that laundered money for the [[Tracksuit Mafia]]. Although Duquesne was quickly released and proven innocent, he learned Eleanor had deceived him and joined Kate, [[Hawkeye]] and their allies in fighting off the Tracksuits during the [[Battle at Rockefeller Center]].

In [[2027]], Duquesne came across someone in need of help and used his swordsmanship to rescue them, being dubbed '''Swordsman''' by the public. He continued his activities as a member of [[New York City]]'s elite, attending fundraisers and balls held by mayor [[Wilson Fisk]]. Duquesne was skeptical of Fisk's involvement in the [[Red Hook Port Revitalization Project]], although Fisk threatened to out Duquesne as Swordsman, leading him to support the project. Later, when Fisk passed his [[Safer Streets Initiative]], Duquesne was detained by the [[Anti-Vigilante Task Force]] and imprisoned.

==Biography==
{{MD|Jack Duquesne (Earth-199999)}}
===Early Life===
====Born into Wealth====
{{Quote|I've never worked a day in my life.|Jack Dequesne to [[Caudle]]|Ronin (episode)}}
Jack Duquesne was born to the wealthy Duquesne family, descendants of the ancient European aristocracy.{{Ref|HE102}} As he has always had money, Duquesne never had to work a day in his life.{{Ref|HE105}} Duquesne developed a fascination with swords, accumulating a large collection of them over the course of his life, as well as training with them and becoming a talented swordsman.{{Ref|HE101}}{{Ref|HE102}} While in {{WPS|Palm Beach, Florida|Palm Beach}}, [[Florida]], Duquesne met and dated a woman named [[Sloan]], whom he found to be a nightmare. Duquesne later broke up with Sloan.{{Ref|HE105}} Duquesne went on vacation with his family to {{WPS|Palm Beach, Florida|Palm Beach}}, where one of his relatives, [[Armand Duquesne VII]], wet himself. Duquesne remembered the moment as a time Armand was embarrassed.{{Ref|HE106}}

===Relationship with the Bishops===
====Meeting Kate Bishop====
[[File:Jack Duquesne & Eleanor Bishop.png|{{AltFloat}}|Duquesne meets [[Kate Bishop]]]]
{{Quote|What's with all the swords, Mom?"<br>"Hon, there have been a few changes while you were away this semester.|[[Kate Bishop]] and [[Eleanor Bishop]]|Never Meet Your Heroes}}
Duquesne began dating [[Eleanor Bishop]], and eventually became engaged to her, unbeknownst to Eleanor's daughter, [[Kate Bishop|Kate]], who was away at college.{{Ref|HE101}} A precautious Duquesne decided to buy a book on being a stepfather to impress her daughter, whom he already knew but ceased to impress.{{Ref|HE102}} In [[2024|December 2024]], Jack Duquesne was at the [[Bishop Residence]] with [[Eleanor Bishop]], preparing for the charity gala, when [[Kate Bishop]] returned.
[[File:Hawkeye101-00124789.png|{{AltFloat}}|Duquesne with [[Eleanor Bishop]] at the gala]]
Kate was surprised, unaware of the relationship between the two. Duquesne left with Eleanor as she told Kate they would talk more at the gala. During the charity gala, Duquesne and Eleanor were speaking with other socialites when Kate approached them, having learned about their relationship. Duquesne left the two to talk, knowing that the conversation was too awkward for him to be there for.{{Ref|HE101}}

====[[Robbery of the Black Market Auction]]====
[[File:Jack Duquesne & Armand Duquesne.png|{{AltFloat}}|Duquesne at the black market auction]]
{{Quote|I'm buying that [[Ronin's Retractable Sword|sword]]."<br>"You don't have three hundred grand."<br>"No, but I'll inherit it one day, won't I?|Jack Duquesne and [[Armand Duquesne III]]|Never Meet Your Heroes}}
Later that night, Duquesne decided to attend the black market auction in the hotel's cellar, sitting next to [[Armand Duquesne III]] despite his uncle's protests. The auctioneer was auctioning off items recovered from the [[Avengers Compound]], such as [[Ronin's Suit|Ronin's suit]] and [[Ronin's Retractable Sword|sword]]. Deeply interested in adding the sword to his collection, he decided to bid on it.
[[File:Ronin's Sword taken by Jack Duquesne.png|{{AltFloat}}|Duquesne stealing [[Ronin's Retractable Sword|Ronin's sword]]]]
Despite his efforts, his uncle managed to outbid him for the sword. However, the auction was interrupted when the [[Tracksuit Mafia]] bombed their way into the cellar, seeking to steal the valuable merchandise the auction was selling. Seeking an advantage within the chaos, Duquesne found the sword in the mess, before rejoining with his uncle to escape the cellar.
[[File:Jack & Armand Duquesne.png|{{AltFloat}}|Duquesne is stopped by the [[Tracksuit Mafia|Tracksuits]]]]
They were momentarily stopped by a Tracksuit member, until [[Kate Bishop]], who was disguised in the [[Ronin's Suit|Ronin Suit]], knocked out the criminal, allowing the Duquesnes to escape. Once back up to the charity gala, Duquesne rejoined [[Eleanor Bishop]], who was looking for her daughter amidst the chaos.{{Ref|HE101}}

====Interrogated by Kate Bishop====
[[File:Jack Duquesne and Eleanor Bishop - Hawkeye 102.jpeg|{{AltFloat}}|Duquesne with [[Eleanor Bishop]] in her [[Bishop Security Headquarters|office]]]]
{{Quote|Oh, but, dear, I think a common interest is very fertile ground for bonding.|Jack Duquesne to [[Eleanor Bishop]]|Hide and Seek}}
The next day, Duquesne went with [[Eleanor Bishop]] to [[Bishop Security Headquarters]] and sat down in her office. They were met by [[Kate Bishop|Kate]], who offered her condolences to Duquesne for his [[Armand Duquesne III|uncle]]'s death. She began to press Duquesne about his inheritance before being interrupted by her mother.
[[File:Jack (Bishop Security HQ).png|{{AltFloat}}|Duquesne discusses being a stepfather]]
As Eleanor asked about the fire in Kate's [[Kate Bishop's Apartment|apartment]], Kate requested that they continue the conversation without Duquesne's presence. However, he analyzed that Kate likely just felt displaced by Duquesne's new role in the family and that it makes sense that Kate would be hostile towards him, things he learned in a book about being a stepfather that he had purchased.{{Ref|HE102}}

====Dinner and Swords====
[[File:Jack Duquesne (12.20.24).png|{{AltFloat}}|Duquesne talking to [[Kate Bishop]]]]
{{Quote|What are you hiding, Jack?"<br>"Nothing. I'm an open book.|[[Kate Bishop]] and Jack Duquesne|Hide and Seek}}
Eleanor invited Kate to come to dinner that night with her and Duquesne to continue their conversations. At dinner that night, the Bishops and Duquesne ate a meal that he had prepared. Kate complimented him on the risotto before the two began discussing his affinity for swords.
[[File:Jack Duquesne the Swordsman.png|{{AltFloat}}|Duquesne dueling against [[Kate Bishop]]]]
Kate challenged Duquesne to a fencing match, and despite Eleanor's disapproval, Duquesne accepted. After changing into fencing gear, the two proceeded to duel. Duquesne let Kate win and she became upset due to Duquesne hiding his expert swordsmanship. Kate became desperate trying to get her mother to see that Duquesne was lying.
[[File:Jack offers Kate butterscotch.png|{{AltFloat}}|Duquesne offers [[Kate Bishop]] butterscotch]]
When Duquesne briefly took his helmet off and turned away from Kate, she attempted to stab him in the face, resulting in Duquesne skillfully parrying her despite not looking at her, proving he was a much more talented swordsman than he was letting on. After the duel, Duquesne changed out of the fencing outfit and tried to ease Kate's concerns about him. When she did not believe him, he offered her a butterscotch with his uncle's emblem. When Kate saw this, she immediately left the house.{{Ref|HE102}}

====Meeting Hawkeye====
[[File:Swordsman and Hawkeye.png|{{AltFloat}}|Duquesne threatens [[Clint Barton]]]]
{{Quote|Oh, my God. You're... You're Archer!"<br>"Hawkeye."<br>"Clint.|Jack Duquesne, [[Kate Bishop]], and [[Clint Barton]]|Partners, Am I Right?}}
The next day, Duquesne was inside the [[Bishop Residence]] as [[Kate Bishop]], [[Clint Barton]], and [[Lucky the Pizza Dog|Lucky]] sneaked in in to investigate him and the [[Tracksuit Mafia]] on the [[Bishop Security]] database. As Barton explored the penthouse, he was caught off guard by Duquesne holding his [[Ronin's Retractable Sword|retractable sword]] to his throat and threatening Barton not to move.{{Ref|HE103}}
[[File:Jack Duquesne meets Clint Barton.png|thumb|{{AltFloat}}|Duquesne realises who [[Clint Barton]] is]]
Kate rushed into the room to stop Duquesne, just as Eleanor entered the room as well. Duquesne then set the sword down against the wall. After Eleanor called Barton an [[Avengers|Avenger]], Duquesne recognized Barton as a superhero, albeit misremembering his codename.
[[File:Eleanor Bishop & Jack Duquesne.png|{{AltFloat}}|Duquesne speaking with [[Kate Bishop|Kate]] and [[Clint Barton|Barton]]]]
The four then sat down at the kitchen table, so Eleanor could ask them why they were sneaking into the penthouse. Kate explained that she was working with Barton on a mission and needed to access the Bishop Security database to obtain information. When Kate stood up to leave, Eleanor requested that Barton leave instead and that Kate stay to further discuss matters.
[[File:Eleanor & Jack dancing.png|{{AltFloat}}|Duquesne dances with [[Eleanor Bishop]]]]
Duquesne entered the living room and joined Eleanor, Kate, and Lucky there. After hearing Eleanor tell Kate about helping set up a Christmas party, Duquesne got excited, requesting that there would be dancing. Kate replied that Eleanor didn't dance, but Duquesne requested a dance with his fiancée anyways, serenading her in the process. As they danced, he sang along to a Christmas song.
[[File:Eleanor & Jack.png|thumb|{{AltFloat}}|Duquesne shares a laugh with the Bishops]]
Afterwards, Eleanor and Kate laughed at Duquesne's tendency to misquote aphorisms, to which Duquesne declared he would rather be laughed at by them than to be alone for the holidays.{{Ref|HE104}}

====Arrested by the NYPD====
[[File:Arrest of Jack Duquesne.png|{{AltFloat}}|Duquesne is arrested by the [[NYPD]]]]
{{Quote|I've obviously been framed. I'll clear all this up and be back in a jiffy for your Christmas party, you'll see.|Jack Duquesne to [[Eleanor Bishop]]|Ronin (episode)}}
Once [[Kate Bishop]]'s investigation into Duquesne unveiled that he was the CEO for a shell corporation, she revealed the information to her [[Eleanor Bishop|mother]], who verified the information and called the [[NYPD]] on Duquesne. Detectives [[Caudle]] and [[Rivera (NYPD)|Rivera]] showed up at the Bishops' [[Bishop Residence|penthouse]] to arrest Duquesne. Duquesne remained calm, claiming that he is likely being framed, as he had no knowledge of [[Sloan Limited]]. He reassured his fiancée that he would get the situation cleared up and be out of police custody in just a short while.{{Ref|HE105}}

====Eleanor Bishop's Christmas Party====
[[File:Swordsman (December 24, 2024).png|{{AltFloat}}|Duquesne attends [[Eleanor Bishop|Bishop]]'s holiday party]]
{{Quote|Wow, Jack's out of jail already. Nothing phases that guy."<br>"So Jack, wielding a sword, just out of jail for allegedly murdering somebody with one.|[[Kate Bishop]] and [[Clint Barton]]|So This Is Christmas?}}
As he promised he would be, Duquesne was freed from [[NYPD]] custody within the next day, having his bail paid for by the father of [[Armand Duquesne VII]]. On Christmas Eve, Duquesne attended the Bishop Christmas Party, to the surprise of [[Clint Barton]], [[Kate Bishop]], and [[Armand Duquesne VII]], who all believed Duquesne to still be in jail. Duquesne was greeted by Armand VII, who inquired about his freedom.
[[File:Jack Duquesne & Armand Duquesne VII.png|{{AltFloat}}|Duquesne speaking with [[Armand Duquesne VII|Armand VII]]]]
Duquesne explained that Armand VII's father had paid his bail, to Armand VII's disappointment as his mother had promised him Duquesne's wine collection. When Armand VII expressed his desire for Duquesne to go back to jail so he can obtain his wine collection, Duquesne embarrassed his relative by reminding him of the time he peed in his pants at [[The Hamptons]].
[[File:Jack Duquesne (30 Rock).png|{{AltFloat}}|Duquesne is dismissed by [[Eleanor Bishop]]]]
Duquesne later found [[Eleanor Bishop]] while she was talking to her daughter, seeking to have a conversation with his fiancée over the events that had transpired over the last day, but was dismissed as she was busy with her argument with her daughter.{{Ref|HE106}}

====[[Battle at Rockefeller Center]]====
[[File:Swordsman (Rockefeller Center).png|{{AltFloat}}|Duquesne fighting against the [[Tracksuit Mafia|Tracksuits]]]]
{{Quote|Okay Jack, this is it. It's your time.|Jack Duquesne|So This Is Christmas?}}
Duquesne and the Bishops heard shots fired from elsewhere in the building. [[Kate Bishop]] told Duquesne and her [[Eleanor Bishop|mother]] to stay where they were as she left. Duquesne turned around to realize that his fiancée had also left, leaving Duquesne alone. Hearing the chaos that was ensuing in the building, Duquesne drew his sword and prepared for battle.
[[File:JackDuquesne-RockefellerCenter.png|{{AltFloat}}|Duquesne makes peace with [[Kate Bishop]]]]
Outside the center, Duquesne arrived in time to disarm and knock out [[Enrique]], who was approaching Kate Bishop with a gun. Bishop apologized for her mother framing him and having him arrested, and asked if Duquesne was doing okay. Duquesne stated he had never been better and continued to fight off the assailing [[Tracksuit Mafia]] members as he told Bishop that he had lost track of her mother. Duquesne continued to fight off the Tracksuits. When Bishop was delegating to the [[NYC LARPers]] to clear the area of civilians, [[Wendy Conrad]] asked if Duquesne was included in that group. Bishop responded that despite Duquesne fighting on their side, they should probably evacuate him as well.
[[File:Jack Duquesne & Wendy Conrad.png|{{AltFloat}}|Duquesne speaking with [[Wendy Conrad]]]]
In the conclusion of the battle, Eleanor Bishop was arrested for the murder of [[Armand Duquesne III]], clearing Duquesne's name of the allegations relating to the murder and any connection to Tracksuit Mafia. As the first responders took over the scene of the battle, Duquesne sat next to Conrad. Conrad, having noticed Duquesne's skill with swords during the battle, asked Duquesne if he had ever heard of LARPing. Duquesne asked if LARPing was a sort of leisure activity, and Conrad tried to invite him to her guild, but Duquesne interrupted her when he got distracted by blood on his tie.{{Ref|HE106}}

===Vigilante Exploits===
====Becoming Swordsman====
[[File:Swordsman footage.png|{{AltFloat}}|Swordsman stops a group of attackers]]
{{Quote|Bro, look how crazy that is. Like, where do you learn that? Kinda looks like a swordsman. Swordsman, if you're watching this, keep doing the good work, because our cops here... they don't really do much, so...|New Yorker|Excessive Force}}
In [[2027|March 2027]], Duquesne started to gain public awareness as he fought publicly with swords. His rescue of a woman from a group of attackers was recorded and shown on ''[[The BB Report]]'', where one New Yorker dubbed him as Swordsman.{{Ref|DDBA106}}

====Meeting Wilson Fisk====
[[File:Jack Duquesne speaks to Wilson Fisk.jpg|{{AltFloat}}|Duquesne gives a warning to [[Wilson Fisk]]]]
{{Quote|Underestimate the people in this room at your own peril. They may not use garrotes or cement shoes. One phone call to the right person, and well... Bye-bye, [[Gracie Mansion]].|Jack Duquesne to [[Wilson Fisk]]|Excessive Force}}
Duquesne was invited to an event with the rest of [[New York]]'s elite to meet with Mayor [[Wilson Fisk]]. Duquesne spoke with Fisk, telling him that he did not agree with the changes he was making to the [[NYPD]] or his stance against vigilantes. Duquesne also noted that Fisk's [[Red Hook Port]] project did not align with the interests of the elite. Fisk defended his choices, but Duquesne warned Fisk of the elite's influence, stating that they could easily take away Fisk's mayorship.{{Ref|DDBA106}}

====Threatened by Wilson Fisk====
[[File:Jack talks to Artemis.png|{{AltFloat}}|Duquesne is concerned for [[Artemis Sledge]]]]
{{Quote|Shall I call you Swordsman, the vigilante?"<br>"Even if I knew what you were talking about, that sort of thing would be an isolated incident."<br>"Hmm. Yet still probable cause for a visit from my [[Anti-Vigilante Task Force|Task Force]].|[[Wilson Fisk]] and Jack Duquesne|Isle of Joy}}
Duquesne was invited to [[Wilson Fisk]]'s [[Black & White Ball]], where he encountered [[Artemis Sledge]]. Duquesne asked about her [[Arthur Sledge|husband]]'s whereabouts, but she did not know, leaving Duquesne confused as she walked away.
[[File:Kingpin & Jack Duquesne.png|{{AltFloat}}|Duquesne is threatened by [[Wilson Fisk]]]]
Duquesne met with Fisk again and was asked to speak privately with the mayor in another room. Duquesne commented on him underestimating Fisk and his [[Red Hook Port Revitalization Project]], leading Fisk to ask how much support Duquesne would be offering for it. Duquesne went to refuse, but Fisk revealed he knew Duquesne was Swordsman and threatened to have his [[Anti-Vigilante Task Force]] go after him. Duquesne was forced to comply with Fisk and then left the event.{{Ref|DDBA108}}

====Kingpin's Prisoner====
[[File:Jack Duquesne imprisoned by Wilson Fisk.png|{{AltFloat}}|Duquesne imprisoned in [[Kingpin]]'s [[Wilson Fisk's Dungeon|dungeon]]]]
When [[Wilson Fisk]] passed his [[Safer Streets Initiative]], Duquesne, having become an enemy of Fisk, both as a civilian and a vigilante, was arrested by the [[Anti-Vigilante Task Force]]. Duquesne was taken to Fisk's [[Wilson Fisk's Dungeon|dungeon]], where he was imprisoned in a cage along with several other enemies to the mayor. While in his cage, Duquesne watched as Fisk and his [[Vanessa Fisk|wife]] walked past them.{{Ref|DDBA109}}

==Abilities==
{{Quote|To be fair, I did downplay my skill and repeatedly lie about it.|Jack Duquesne to [[Eleanor Bishop]]|Hide and Seek}}
*'''Sword Mastery''': [[File:Swordsman vs. Tracksuit Mafia.png|thumb|250px|Duquesne fights [[Tracksuit Mafia]] with sword]] Duquesne is extremely skilled at using a sword in combat. He initially held back during his duel with [[Kate Bishop]] in fencing, a two-time state champion, but then he was able to parry a thrust to his face and disarm her without even looking. Bishop later admitted that he was like a professional. During the [[Battle at Rockefeller Center]], he used his sabre to fend off several members of the [[Tracksuit Mafia]], even when they were carrying small arms. Afterwards, he was offered a position with the [[New York City Live Action Role Players]] for his skill.

==Equipment==
===Weapons===
*'''[[Ronin's Retractable Sword]]''': [[File:Jack Duquesne steals the Ronin Sword.png|thumb|250px|Duquesne with [[Ronin]]'s [[Ronin's Retractable Sword|sword]]]] After his [[Armand Duquesne III|uncle]] bid on Ronin's retractable sword at the black market auction, Duquesne stole the item after the event was disrupted. He later used it to threaten [[Clint Barton]] in Eleanor's penthouse, but he lowered his guard once he realized he was a friend of his future stepdaughter. The sword was later covertly reclaimed by Barton.
*'''Fencing Sword''': Duquesne owns a fencing sword which he used during his sparring match with [[Kate Bishop]].
*'''Sabre''': Jack used a sabre to fight off many members of the Tracksuit Mafia. He also uses it during his ventures as the vigilante Swordsman.

===Other Equipment===
*'''Fencing Uniform''': Duquesne wore a fencing uniform during his match with [[Kate Bishop]], including a mask, jacket, breeches, and a single glove.

==Facilities==
{{Expand}}
*'''[[Bishop Residence]]''': Since beginning his relationship with [[Eleanor Bishop]], Duquesne spends a lot of time at the Bishops' penthouse, having moved some of his sword collection to the building.
